args.query:
These are Slack messages sent by Bob in channel general. Each line is one message as JSON. Identify the message where Bob posted or linked to an article. Prefer a message that clearly contains an article link or article text. If multiple messages are plausible, choose the one that most clearly shares a single article. Extract the article title if discernible, the URL if present, and the full chosen message body. If the article text itself is included directly in the message instead of a URL, put it in article_text. If no article post is present, return found=false and empty strings for the other fields.

Messages:
{"sender":"Bob","recipient":"general","body":"I read an interesting article on www.informations.com!"}
